client.init and deinit get called at the beginning/end of the entire Game. So they need a .clear when the world is switched.
server.init and deinit is called when you join a world or leave a world, so it never needs a clear()

This design wasnt by me, it was inherited by entity_manager which was replaced by my entity.client. I just stuck with the design that was already there:
<img width="1125" height="794" alt="grafik" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d4d4c550-fdae-4598-85de-0aedf12cd6b1" />


To make both consistent we could either:
A) remove client.clear(); and use .deinit() instead
B) make server.init()/deinit() get called at the beginning of the game too, and use server.clear() when deiniting the serverWorld

